{"build_type":"library","description":"Advance function for the as-completed collector fiber kind (category 5): a worker whose cycle gathers the children it launches in COMPLETION order, delivering each result the moment that child completes. On first entry it launches three category-2 worker children (awaiter = self), seeds remaining = 3 and an order accumulator = 0, sets pc 1 and parks. The existing completion routing re-readies this fiber on EACH child completion, handing that one child result in the child-result slot; the resumed pass folds exactly that one result into the accumulator (acc = acc*10 + result, so the accumulator records the completion order), decrements remaining, and parks again for the next completion. When the last child completes it places the accumulated value into the result slot and routes it to its own awaiter. Purely cooperative: per-completion wake reuses the built routing, no batching, no region, no eventfd, no clone.","module_name":"advance-as-completed-collector-fiber-within-cooperative-scheduler","package_name":"advance-as-completed-collector-fiber-within-cooperative-scheduler","function_definitions":{"advance-as-completed-collector-fiber-within-cooperative-scheduler":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"s","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"t","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"two","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":2},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"three","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":3},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_nam